longBusinessSummary: Resource Capital Gold Corp. engages in the exploration, development, and production of precious metal properties in North America. The company primarily develops and produces gold and silver assets. It holds 90% interest in the Tangier Gold mine, Forest Hill mine, and Dufferin Gold mine located in Nova Scotia. The company was formerly known as Reliance Resources Limited and changed its name to Resource Capital Gold Corp. in February 2016. Resource Capital Gold Corp. was incorporated in 1989 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
